Click Here
		to meet with us
 




 


 


 Wealth ManagerGrubman Wealth Management is a wealth management firm located in downtown Berkeley.  We provide investment management, financial planning and tax services to over 135 families and individuals managing over $250 million of client assets.
We seek an experienced CFP® to provide advisory services to our clients including retirement planning, education funding, budgeting, liability and asset management, and other issues relating to personal financial management.  The services range from presenting comprehensive financial plans to providing investment updates and ad hoc financial advice.
The candidate must enjoy working as part of a team of CFPs®, CPAs and CFA® charterholders, learning new material, teaching coworkers and clients, and providing analysis and recommendations to our clients.
The position reports to the firm’s founder and president.
Compensation consists of a base salary and employment benefits, with significant upside potential and the opportunity to become a firm principal.
Qualifications:
CFP® required
Bachelor’s degree, minimum 3.4 GPA
Experienced relationship management
Proven ability to produce accurate work product
Proficiency in Word, Excel and CRM programs
Be a quick adopter of new IT
Must have excellent written and verbal communication skills
		 
 






 












