Our Team | Grubman Wealth Management - Berkeley






























 


Grubman Wealth ManagementIndependent Investment Management
Our Team
We’re a small team of handpicked professionals committed to staying by your side throughout your lifelong financial journey, offering familiar faces and consistent advice as you clarify and navigate your financial goals. Our highly skilled staff currently consists of financial planners, investment experts and tax professionals — along with a wonderful administrative staff that includes our operations manager and client service professionals.
To get to know us better, click on a team member’s photo and read their bio. We invite you to contact us today to come in for an initial consultation.
 







Audrey Grubman, CFP®
President, Wealth Manager




Audrey Grubman, CFP®
President, Wealth Manager
From her studies of physics at MIT and her professional background in accounting, product development, and software management, Audrey Grubman charted an intuitive course to become a Certified Financial Planner and business owner. In the early 1990s she began to offer stock option planning to employees of PeopleSoft, an early leader in human resources, financial, and enterprise management software. Her success in this endeavor eventually grew into the official launch of Grubman Financial Consulting in 1996. Audrey has since grown her grassroots little firm into a well-respected, full-service business called Grubman Wealth Management, offering financial planning, investment management and tax services under one roof.
She earned a Certificate in Personal Financial Planning with Distinction from the University of California, Berkeley Extension School and is a member of the Financial Planning Association and the East Bay Estate Planning Council.







David Born, CFA, CFP®
Portfolio Manager, Wealth Manager




David Born, CFA, CFP®
Portfolio Manager, Wealth Manager
David began his career in 2007 in Morgan Stanley’s financial advisor training program, moving to HighMark Capital Management, a subsidiary of Union Bank, progressing from internal wholesaler of HighMark mutual funds to Assistant Vice President and Assistant Portfolio Manager.  David earned his bachelor’s degree from the University of California Berkeley with concentrations in Finance and Economics.  After taking a sabbatical to pursue his dream of traveling the world, David is happy to return to his roots in the Bay Area. 
In his free time David enjoys spending time with family and friends, drinking a good coffee, playing water polo, and hiking with his dog.







Dillon McGill, CFP®
Wealth Manager




Dillon McGill, CFP®
Wealth Manager
Dillon started his career in wealth management as a member of the operations group for an independent advisory firm. His passion is listening to clients as they share their life experiences, learning what they care about most so he can better help them achieve their goals. As a Wealth Manager deeply committed to our investment process and the success of each and every one of our clients, he is a great addition to the Grubman team.
Dillon earned a Bachelor of Science in Kinesiology from California Polytechnic State University, San Luis Obispo, and holds professional certificates in Personal Financial Planning and Accounting from the University of California Santa Barbara’s University Extension. He is a member of the Financial Planning Association (FPA) and is the Social Media Coordinator of the FPA NexGen national leadership team.
Outside of work, Dillon enjoys spending time with his family and friends, participating in action sports like motocross, listening to music, and taking photographs.







Jill Martin
Operations Manager




Jill Martin
Operations Manager
Having worn many hats at Grubman Wealth Management over the years, Jill now ensures the smooth operation of all processes and services delivery for GWM. She earned a BA in Sociology from UC Berkeley and a JD from Boalt Hall School of Law.







Daniel Leong, EA
Tax Manager




Daniel Leong, EA
Tax Manager
Dan has been a tax specialist since 2000. Prior to joining Grubman Wealth Management in 2014, he worked at various small public accounting and tax preparation firms throughout the Bay Area. He has extensive experience providing personalized service to high-net-worth individuals, including those with small business interests, trusts and taxable estates.
Dan earned his bachelor’s degree from the University of California at San Diego and has completed graduate course work in taxation at Golden Gate University. His previous endeavors include a decade of high performance coaching in the sport of badminton, including Olympic player development for USA Badminton.







Hansson Ling, EA
Senior Tax Accountant




Hansson Ling, EA
Senior Tax Accountant
Hansson has been a tax specialist since 2001. Before joining Grubman Wealth Management, he worked at various local public accounting and tax attorney firms in the Bay Area. His experience includes providing tax consulting and compliance services for high-net-worth individuals and small business entities.
Hansson earned his bachelor’s degree from California State University, Hayward, with a major in accounting. Outside of work, Hansson loves to play basketball and baseball with his three young boys at home and to spend quality time with his family.







Collin Hoover
Client Service Representative




Collin Hoover
Client Service Representative
Collin joined Grubman Wealth Management in 2015. He graduated from the University of Puget Sound with a bachelor’s degree in economics and a minor in music. His primary roles within the company are handling client calls and requests and performing a variety of administrative tasks. In his spare time, he pursues various martial arts styles.







William Lew
Client Service Representative




William Lew
Client Service Representative
Will joined Grubman Wealth Management in 2007, and works closely with our new clients, helping welcome and orient them to our firm. He also spearheads setting up investment management accounts, distributing quarterly statements and invoices, handling clients’ money-movement requests, maintaining client files and processing tax returns and other tax forms.
Outside of work, Will coaches basketball at Oakland High School, where he has taught basketball and life skills to many young men, most of whom have parlayed his lessons into successful college and life experiences.





